body:
Well I used proxy functionality... This change forces to write more code.
My solution is to create MyClassProxy as extension or as decorator for MyClass.
Real example:
```php
final class FlysystemProxy extends Filesystem
{
    /** @var MockObject<Filesystem>|null */
    private (MockObject&Filesystem)|null $mock;

    public function withMock(MockObject&Filesystem $mock): void
    {
        $this->mock = $mock;
    }

    public function expects(InvocationOrder $invocationOrder): InvocationStubber
    {
        return $this->mock->expects($invocationOrder);
    }

    #[Override]
    public function publicUrl(string $path, array $config = []): string
    {
        $this->mock?->publicUrl($path, $config);

        return parent::publicUrl($path, $config);
    }

    #[Override]
    public function temporaryUrl(string $path, DateTimeInterface $expiresAt, array $config = []): string
    {
        $this->mock?->temporaryUrl($path, $expiresAt, $config);

        return parent::temporaryUrl($path, $expiresAt, $config);
    }

    // ... lots of overridden methods (that were generated by AI, otherwise I would have to write it by hand)
}
```
this is initialized in `setUp()` like:
```php
        $this->flysystem = new FlysystemProxy(
            adapter: $this->inMemoryAdapter,
            publicUrlGenerator: new class implements PublicUrlGenerator {
                public function publicUrl(string $path, Config $config): string
                {
                    return 'public_url';
                }
            },
            temporaryUrlGenerator: new class implements TemporaryUrlGenerator {
                public function temporaryUrl(string $path, DateTimeInterface $expiresAt, Config $config): string
                {
                    return 'temporary_url';
                }
            },
        );
        $this->flysystem->withMock(
            $this->createMock(Filesystem::class),
        );
```
and then I can put expectations on it just like if it would be a mock with `enableProxyingToOriginalMethods` enabled:
```php
        $this->flysystem->expects($this->once())
            ->method('setVisibility')
            ->willThrowException($exception);
```
